						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">No king: A.D. 1303.</hi> </p>						

						<p>Damaged. A symbol of sun engraved at the beginning of the inscription. Gift of three <hi rend="italic">guḷakams</hi> (in symbol ?) of land for maintaining one perpetual lamp to the presiding deity, Vīṟṟiruntha Perumāḷ, in the temple at the village, Koḷḷagar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tribhuvanamahādēvichchaturvēdimaṅgalam, by Pulvēḷuruḍaiyār, a person holding the right of accountantship <hi rend="italic">(kaṇakkak-kāṇiyāḷaṉ)</hi> of the village. The land was given to Kōvalakkūtta Nambiyār, the priest in the temple for maintenance.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">E.C.</hi> (n), Vol. IV, No. Kol. 6.</p>						

